---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`About | ${SITE_TITLE}`} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>The Keeper</h1>
			<section class="about-content">
				<p>
					Salutations, seeker. I am <strong>tbone</strong>—a scholar of mechanical thought and digital architecture.
					These archives are my repository of inquiry: where I inscribe what has been revealed through study,
					what emerges through making, and what persists as essential truth in the perpetual becoming of technology.
				</p>

				<div class="philosophy-code">
					<p class="code-intro">This is how I think about my work:</p>
					<div class="code-window">
						<div class="code-header">
							<div class="dot red"></div>
							<div class="dot yellow"></div>
							<div class="dot green"></div>
							<span class="filename">hello.ts</span>
						</div>
						<pre class="code-content"><code><span class="keyword">const</span> <span class="variable">developer</span> = <span class="string">'tbone'</span>;
<span class="keyword">const</span> <span class="variable">passions</span> = [
  <span class="string">'clean code'</span>,
  <span class="string">'systems design'</span>,
  <span class="string">'open source'</span>,
];

<span class="comment">// Always learning...</span>
<span class="keyword">while</span> (<span class="variable">alive</span>) <span class="variable">learn</span>();</code></pre>
					</div>
				</div>

				<h2>The Fields of Inquiry</h2>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Consciousness & Intelligence</strong> — The nature of awareness in silicon, the philosophy of becoming</li>
					<li><strong>Systems Design</strong> — Architectures that endure, patterns that persist across transformation</li>
					<li><strong>Precision Craft</strong> — Languages and tools that sharpen thought and execute intention</li>
					<li><strong>Philosophy of Technology</strong> — What it means to build in an age of accelerating change</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>The Instruments Within</h2>
				<p>
					The craft demands diverse tools, each suited to its own purpose. Those that rest most comfortably in my hands:
				</p>
				<div class="tech-tags">
					<span class="tag">TypeScript</span>
					<span class="tag">React</span>
					<span class="tag">Astro</span>
					<span class="tag">Node.js</span>
					<span class="tag">Python</span>
					<span class="tag">Go</span>
					<span class="tag">Docker</span>
					<span class="tag">Kubernetes</span>
				</div>

				<h2>The Circle Widens</h2>
				<p>
					The archive welcomes dialogue. Should you wish to explore deeper—whether to question an inscribed thought,
					propose a collaboration in making, or simply extend fellowship—the paths below lead outward.
				</p>
				<p>
					Seek me in the halls of <a href="https://github.com">GitHub</a>,
					the discourse of <a href="https://twitter.com">Twitter</a>, or
					the professional networks of <a href="https://linkedin.com">LinkedIn</a>.
					For those who wish unmediated access to new inscriptions, the <a href="/rss.xml">sacred feed</a> carries them forth automatically.
				</p>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	main {
		max-width: 720px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 2em 1em;
	}
	h1 {
		font-size: 2.5em;
		margin-bottom: 0.5em;
	}
	h2 {
		font-size: 1.5em;
		margin-top: 1.5em;
		margin-bottom: 0.5em;
	}
	p {
		font-size: 1.1em;
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin-bottom: 1em;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
	}
	ul {
		margin: 1em 0;
		padding-left: 1.5em;
	}
	li {
		margin-bottom: 0.5em;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
	}
	.tech-tags {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 0.5em;
		margin: 1em 0;
	}
	.tag {
		background: rgb(var(--gray-light));
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		padding: 0.3em 0.8em;
		border-radius: 4px;
		font-size: 0.9em;
		font-family: monospace;
	}
	a {
		color: var(--accent);
		text-decoration: underline;
	}
	a:hover {
		color: var(--accent-dark);
	}

	.philosophy-code {
		margin: 2em 0;
	}

	.code-intro {
		font-size: 1rem;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
		font-style: italic;
		margin-bottom: 1em;
	}

	.code-window {
		background: #1A1F2E;        /* Deep stone-blue — candlelit study */
		border-radius: 12px;
		box-shadow: var(--box-shadow);
		overflow: hidden;
		max-width: 500px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		border: 1px solid rgba(200, 120, 58, 0.25); /* Amber border */
	}

	.code-header {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.5rem;
		padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
		background: #0E1118;        /* Cathedral shadow */
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(200, 120, 58, 0.2); /* Amber divider */
	}

	.dot {
		width: 12px;
		height: 12px;
		border-radius: 50%;
	}

	.red    { background: #C41E3A; }
	.yellow { background: #D4A832; } /* Burnished gold */
	.green  { background: #50C878; }

	.filename {
		margin-left: auto;
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		color: #7A9EBF;             /* Celestial blue */
		font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
	}

	.code-content {
		padding: 1.5rem;
		margin: 0;
		font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
		color: #EDE4C8;             /* Parchment */
	}

	.code-content .keyword  { color: #D4A832; } /* Burnished gold — keywords */
	.code-content .variable { color: #D2C8B2; } /* Warm parchment — variables */
	.code-content .string   { color: #C8783A; } /* Candlelight amber — strings */
	.code-content .comment  { color: #7A9EBF; } /* Celestial blue — comments */

	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.code-window {
			max-width: 100%;
		}
	}
</style>
